Niantic keeps deleting my reviews. I played this game since it first came out back in 2016. Went inactive for a whie before picking it up back 2020 That being said, the game was very interesting in the beginning with the opportunities to capture Pokemon in our reality using AR technology. That being said, it can be buggy sometimes costing precious raid tickets, if you are into raiding. There are also bugs related to PvP experience though I do not experience it that much. I also do not enjoy the regional mechanics. I understand it works in the original game series but who has money lying around to travel from Australia to Hawaii searching for Relicanths and Comfeys? Not this guy!! Furthermore, the latest updates really screwed players over especially the decrease in incense functionality. It puts a damper on the gaming experience especially for rural and disabled players, which says a lot about Niantic's unwillingness to listen or even acknowledge its users. The game itself also siphons money faster than a student loan payment on steroids but if you're okay with that sort of stuff, knock yourselves out. Overall 1/5. The game graphics, although eye-catching, does not excuse the bug-filled game designs, the idiotic regional mechanics, the lack of care from Niantic as exemplified by its updates and lack of cohesion between the game developers and its users, and the pressing pressure that you have to spend money to get anywhere in this game.
